## Data Partitioning

set.seed(2)

reorder = sample(1:n, n, replace=FALSE)

X = X[reorder, ]
Y = Y[reorder]

n_learn = 850
n_test = n - n_learn

Y_test = Y[1:n_test]
Y_learn = Y[(n_test+1):(n_test+n_learn)]

X_test = X[1:n_test, ]
X_learn = X[(n_test+1):(n_test+n_learn), ]



## OLS Regression

ols_names <- c("Intercept", colnames(X))
ols_reg <- lm(Y_learn ~., data = X_learn)
ols_coef <- ols_reg$coefficients |>
  cbind(ols_names) |>
  as_tibble() |>
  rename(coefficient = ols_names, slope = V1) |>
  mutate(
    slope = as.double(slope),
    coefficient = fct_reorder(coefficient, desc(slope))) |>
  filter(coefficient != "Intercept")
## Warning: The `x` argument of `as_tibble.matrix()` must have unique column names if
## `.name_repair` is omitted as of tibble 2.0.0.
## ℹ Using compatibility `.name_repair`.
## This warning is displayed once every 8 hours.
## Call `lifecycle::last_lifecycle_warnings()` to see where this warning was
## generated.
ols_coef |>
  ggplot(aes(coefficient, slope)) +
  geom_bar(stat='identity', fill = case_when(
    ols_coef$slope < 0 ~ "red",
    .default = "green"
  ), color = case_when(
    ols_coef$slope < 0 ~ "darkred",
    .default = "darkgreen"
  )) +
  labs(x = "Feature", y = "Slope", title = "OLS Regression Fit") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(size = 14), axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, vjust = 1, hjust=1, size = 10))

Y_pred <- predict(ols_reg, X_test)

ols_mse = mean((Y_test - Y_pred)^2)

baseline_mse = mean((Y_test - mean(Y_learn))^2)

dev.off()

## Lasso Regression

library(glmnet)

## Attaching package: 'Matrix'

## Loaded glmnet 4.1-8
cv_model <- cv.glmnet(as.matrix(X_learn), Y_learn, alpha = 0, nfolds = 5)
optimal_lambda <- cv_model$lambda.min

## Lasso model 

lasso_model <- glmnet(X_learn, Y_learn, alpha = 0, lambda = optimal_lambda)

print(coef(lasso_model))
## 10 x 1 sparse Matrix of class "dgCMatrix"
##                                    s0
## (Intercept)              0.5174165192
## fourth_down_pct         -0.0173246602

## interceptions_per_game   0.0311564502
predictions <- predict(lasso_model, newx = as.matrix(X_test), s = optimal_lambda)

lasso_mse <- mean((predictions - Y_test )^2)
